### ============================================================
###  Health Tracking API — Example Requests
###  Compatible with VS Code REST Client extension
###  and JetBrains HTTP Client
###
###  Usage:
###    1. Start server: uvicorn app.main:app --reload
###    2. Run "Signup" and "Login" first
###    3. Copy the access_token into @token below
###    4. Run any other request
### ============================================================

@base_url = http://localhost:8000/api/v1
@token = PASTE_YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  SYSTEM
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health check
GET http://localhost:8000/health-check

### API root
GET http://localhost:8000/


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  AUTH — Signup
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Create a new account
POST {{base_url}}/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "Alice@1234",
  "full_name": "Alice Smith"
}

###
# Expected response (201 Created):
# {
#   "message": "Account created for alice@example.com"
# }


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  AUTH — Login
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 2. Login and receive access token
POST {{base_url}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "password": "Alice@1234"
}

###
# Expected response (200 OK):
# {
#   "access_token": "eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...",
#   "token_type": "bearer"
# }
#
# → Copy the access_token value into @token at the top of this file


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  HEALTH ENTRIES — Create
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 3. Log a full daily health entry (all 6 metrics)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-06-15",
  "sleep_hours": 7.5,
  "steps": 9200,
  "calories_consumed": 2100,
  "water_intake_ml": 2500,
  "stress_level": 4,
  "heart_rate_bpm": 68,
  "notes": "Felt rested. Gym session in the morning.",
  "source": "manual"
}

###
# Expected response (201 Created):
# {
#   "id": "uuid...",
#   "user_id": "uuid...",
#   "entry_date": "2024-06-15",
#   "sleep_hours": 7.5,
#   "steps": 9200,
#   "calories_consumed": 2100,
#   "water_intake_ml": 2500,
#   "stress_level": 4,
#   "heart_rate_bpm": 68,
#   "sleep_minutes": 450,
#   "water_intake_glasses": 10.0,
#   "stress_label": "Mild",
#   "heart_rate_zone": "Excellent (60–70 bpm)",
#   "notes": "Felt rested. Gym session in the morning.",
#   "source": "manual",
#   "created_at": "...",
#   "updated_at": "..."
# }


### 4. Log a PARTIAL entry — sleep only (all other metrics optional)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-06-16",
  "sleep_hours": 6.0
}

###
# Expected response (201 Created) — untracked metrics return null:
# {
#   "sleep_hours": 6.0,
#   "steps": null,
#   "calories_consumed": null,
#   "water_intake_ml": null,
#   "stress_level": null,
#   "heart_rate_bpm": null,
#   "sleep_minutes": 360,
#   ...
# }


### 5. Log from a wearable device (source = fitbit)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-06-17",
  "sleep_hours": 8.2,
  "steps": 11450,
  "heart_rate_bpm": 61,
  "water_intake_ml": 1800,
  "source": "fitbit"
}


### 6. HIGH stress day example
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-06-18",
  "sleep_hours": 5.0,
  "steps": 2100,
  "calories_consumed": 2800,
  "water_intake_ml": 900,
  "stress_level": 9,
  "heart_rate_bpm": 92,
  "notes": "Deadline day. Very little sleep. Stressed."
}

###
# Expected stress_label: "Extreme"
# Expected heart_rate_zone: "Above average (81–90 bpm)"


### 7. ERROR — Missing all metrics (returns 422)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-06-19",
  "notes": "Just a note but no metric data"
}

###
# Expected response (422 Unprocessable Entity):
# {
#   "detail": "Validation failed",
#   "errors": [
#     {
#       "field": "body",
#       "message": "At least one metric ... must be provided",
#       "type": "value_error"
#     }
#   ]
# }


### 8. ERROR — Out-of-range value (stress_level > 10)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-06-20",
  "stress_level": 15
}

###
# Expected response (422 Unprocessable Entity)


### 9. ERROR — Duplicate date (returns 409)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-06-15",
  "steps": 500
}

###
# Expected response (409 Conflict):
# {
#   "detail": "A health entry for 2024-06-15 already exists. Use PATCH to update it."
# }


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  HEALTH ENTRIES — Read
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 10. List all entries (paginated, newest first)
GET {{base_url}}/health
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 11. List with pagination (page 2, 5 items per page)
GET {{base_url}}/health?page=2&size=5
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 12. Filter by date range
GET {{base_url}}/health?start_date=2024-06-01&end_date=2024-06-30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 13. Filter — low stress days only (stress ≤ 3)
GET {{base_url}}/health?max_stress_level=3
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 14. Filter — active days (steps ≥ 8000)
GET {{base_url}}/health?min_steps=8000
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 15. Filter — entries from Fitbit only
GET {{base_url}}/health?source=fitbit
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 16. Combined filters — June 2024, good sleep (≥ 7h), low stress (≤ 4)
GET {{base_url}}/health?start_date=2024-06-01&end_date=2024-06-30&min_sleep_hours=7&max_stress_level=4
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 17. Get today's entry (shortcut)
GET {{base_url}}/health/today
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
# Returns 404 if today hasn't been logged yet


### 18. Get entry by specific date
GET {{base_url}}/health/date/2024-06-15
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 19. Get entry by UUID
# Replace {entry_id} with an actual UUID from a previous response
GET {{base_url}}/health/YOUR_ENTRY_UUID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  HEALTH ENTRIES — Update (PATCH)
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 20. Update steps only (partial update — other fields untouched)
PATCH {{base_url}}/health/YOUR_ENTRY_UUID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "steps": 12000
}


### 21. Update multiple metrics at once
PATCH {{base_url}}/health/YOUR_ENTRY_UUID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "water_intake_ml": 3500,
  "stress_level": 2,
  "heart_rate_bpm": 60,
  "notes": "Went for a long walk. Felt much better."
}


### 22. Update notes only
PATCH {{base_url}}/health/YOUR_ENTRY_UUID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "notes": "Updated journal: meditation helped with stress."
}


### 23. ERROR — Empty PATCH body (returns 422)
PATCH {{base_url}}/health/YOUR_ENTRY_UUID_HERE
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{}

###
# Expected response (422 Unprocessable Entity):
# "At least one field must be provided for update"


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  HEALTH ENTRIES — Delete
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 24. Delete an entry by UUID
DELETE {{base_url}}/health/YOUR_ENTRY_UUID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
# Expected response (200 OK):
# {
#   "message": "Health entry deleted successfully"
# }


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  ANALYTICS — Summary
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 25. Weekly summary (last 7 days)
GET {{base_url}}/health/summary?start_date=2024-06-10&end_date=2024-06-16
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
# Expected response:
# {
#   "period_start": "2024-06-10",
#   "period_end": "2024-06-16",
#   "total_entries": 4,
#   "avg_sleep_hours": 7.18,
#   "min_sleep_hours": 5.0,
#   "max_sleep_hours": 8.2,
#   "avg_steps": 7560.0,
#   "total_steps": 30240,
#   "max_steps": 11450,
#   "avg_calories_consumed": 2450.0,
#   "total_calories_consumed": 9800,
#   "avg_water_intake_ml": 1800.0,
#   "total_water_intake_ml": 7200,
#   "avg_stress_level": 5.5,
#   "min_stress_level": 4,
#   "max_stress_level": 9,
#   "avg_heart_rate_bpm": 72.75,
#   "min_heart_rate_bpm": 61,
#   "max_heart_rate_bpm": 92
# }


### 26. Monthly summary — June 2024
GET {{base_url}}/health/summary?start_date=2024-06-01&end_date=2024-06-30
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}


### 27. ERROR — start_date after end_date (returns 400)
GET {{base_url}}/health/summary?start_date=2024-12-31&end_date=2024-01-01
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
# Expected response (400 Bad Request):
# {
#   "detail": "start_date must not be after end_date"
# }


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  ANALYTICS — Streak
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 28. Get logging streak
GET {{base_url}}/health/streak
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###
# Expected response:
# {
#   "current_streak": 4,
#   "longest_streak": 12,
#   "last_entry_date": "2024-06-18"
# }


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  ERROR EXAMPLES — Validation failures
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### 29. sleep_hours out of range (> 24)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-07-01",
  "sleep_hours": 25.0
}


### 30. heart_rate_bpm out of range (< 30)
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-07-02",
  "heart_rate_bpm": 15
}


### 31. steps negative
POST {{base_url}}/health
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
  "entry_date": "2024-07-03",
  "steps": -100
}


### 32. Unauthenticated request (returns 401)
GET {{base_url}}/health


### 33. Wrong owner — trying to access another user's entry (returns 403)
# Log in as a different user first, then try to access Alice's entry UUID
GET {{base_url}}/health/ALICES_ENTRY_UUID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer OTHER_USERS_TOKEN


### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###  METRIC REFERENCE CARD
### ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  Metric              | Min    | Max     | Unit          | Notes
#  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  sleep_hours         | 0.0    | 24.0    | hours         | Supports decimals (7.5 = 7h 30m)
#  steps               | 0      | 100 000 | steps/day     |
#  calories_consumed   | 0      | 10 000  | kcal          |
#  water_intake_ml     | 0      | 10 000  | ml            | 250 ml = 1 glass
#  stress_level        | 1      | 10      | scale         | 1=none, 10=extreme
#  heart_rate_bpm      | 30     | 250     | bpm           | Resting heart rate
#
#  Computed fields (auto-calculated, never submitted):
#  sleep_minutes        = sleep_hours × 60
#  water_intake_glasses = water_intake_ml / 250
#  stress_label         = Low|Mild|Moderate|High|Extreme
#  heart_rate_zone      = Athlete|Excellent|Good|Above average|High normal|Elevated
#
#  Stress label mapping:
#    1–2  → Low
#    3–4  → Mild
#    5–6  → Moderate
#    7–8  → High
#    9–10 → Extreme
#
#  Heart rate zone mapping:
#    < 60  → Athlete
#    60–70 → Excellent
#    71–80 → Good
#    81–90 → Above average
#    91–100→ High normal
#    > 100 → Elevated (consult a doctor)
